      Parameters/Arguments (Input) 
     ___________________________________
      Functions can but do not have to take input, called parameters
     
     Paraneters work like variables that can be used in the body of the function - however their valurs are typicvally only given when the function is called, not when it is defined
     
     When the value itself is passed to the function, its called  an argument 
     
     Body
     _________________
     
     The body of the function is the code block that goes between the curly braces.
     
     function repeatMessage(message, times) {
           for (var i=0; i < times; i ++) { 
           console.log(message);____________________________LOOP FUNCTION
           }
           }
     
      
